                        <Text layoutX="14.0" layoutY="44.0" lineSpacing="1.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="As COVID-19 swept the world in 2020 and 2021, lives were lost and economies closed. When vaccines were produced in late 2020, we thought that they were the answers to normality. Yet, now at the end of 2021, there still seems to be no end to this ravaging pandemic around the world. It is not that the vaccines are ineffective but that some do not have the chance to get one. Vaccine inequity has caused a huge disparity in vaccine rollouts across the world. " textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="466.9368591308594" />
