                              <TableView fx:id="tableReportC1" layoutX="31.0" layoutY="695.0" prefHeight="149.0" prefWidth="446.0" />
                        <Text layoutX="14.0" layoutY="872.0" lineSpacing="1.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="A COVID-19 vaccine costs from HKD 15 to HKD 300. Not all countries have a healthcare budget to cover this hefty sum. On average, countries with GDP per capita in the first quartile started their vaccinations three months after countries in the last quartile. When the richer countries were close to one dose per person, the poorer countries had only less than 10 doses for every 100 people. " textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="462.93685817718506" />
                              <Text layoutX="14.0" layoutY="971.0" lineSpacing="1.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Economic status is not the only indicator of a successful vaccination campaign. The Human Development Index (HDI) is a metric that reflects the living standards, knowledge acquisition, and life expectancy of a country’s citizens. " textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="466.0" />
